<sentence id="1">IL-17 was first described as a T cell product with proinflammatory properties [ 5,22 ] .</sentence>
<sentence id="2">RA is characterized by hyperplasia of synovial lining cells and an intense infiltration by mononuclear cells [ 23 ] .</sentence>
<sentence id="3">Proinflammatory cytokines such as IL-1 and TNF-alpha are abundant in rheumatoid synovium , whereas the T cell-derived cytokines , especially IL-4 and interferon-gamma , have often proved difficult to detect in RA synovium [ 24 ] .</sentence>
