<sentence id="5">In this respect , IL-17 is appealing because it has been described as a T cell-derived cytokine with proinflammatory properties .</sentence>
<sentence id="6">In our studies , we tried to evaluate how IL-17 production is regulated in RA PBMC , and which signaling pathway it used .</sentence>
<sentence id="7">Levels of IL-17 were found to be higher in RA synovial fluid than in OA synovial fluid [ 15 ] .</sentence>
